<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1357" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1357">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/159.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Hostetter</persName>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Hermosillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-09">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>General Carranza wires regarding the Associated Press reports
                                regarding action of Villa when he gets to Torreon in treatment of
                                    <pb facs="0908" n="792" xml:id="pg_792"/> Spaniards: Carranza
                                says Associated Press is not always to be believed, and he does not
                                believe Villa made said statements, as he has notified chief that
                                all foreigners and their properties will be respected.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hostetter</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>